refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
public intSplFileObject::fseek intoffset intwhenceSEEK_SET
Seek to a position in the file measured in bytes from the beginning of the file, obtained by adding offset to the position specified by whence.

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 Returns 0 if the seek was successful, -1 otherwise. Note that seeking
 past EOF is not considered an error.

  &reftitle.examples;



    SplFileObject::fseek example


<?php
$file = new SplFileInfo("somefile.txt");

// Read first line
$data = $file->fgets();

// Move back to the beginning of the file
// Same as $file->rewind();
$file->fseek(0);
?>
